CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: A1 - Party
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Party Subject Area shows that all persons, organizations, and groups can be represented as "parties" and that parties can then be related to other major objects with specified roles. The Party design also provides for a common approach to describing communication identifiers, relationships between parties, and legal identifiers. Examples of the use of the party types is also shown.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: A2 - Account and Agreement
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Account and Agreement Subject Area presents the common framework for establishing customer-oriented accounts and company-oriented financial services agreements. Party Role is used to relate all parties to account and agreement, and various agreement types are identified. Refer to the Agreement Role Subject Area for examples of the roles involved with agreements.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: A3 - Policy
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Policy Subject Area defines the common features of an insurance policy and shows how they are related to parties and agreement. Common constructs for Geographic Location and Insurable Objects allow for these to be shared above the level of a Policy. A common entity for policy monies allows for all types of amounts to be defined at all policy levels.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: A4 - Claim
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Claim Subject Area defines the major entities involved in claims management, beginning with an occurrence resulting in claims and subclaims, and the option of arbitration and litigation being involved in claim settlement. As with all areas of the model, the relationships and roles of parties is defined for the major entities. The relationship of claim to coverage is shown, and a common entity for all claims monies is defined. Refer to the Claim Role Subject Area for examples of the roles involved wtih claims.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: A5 - Assessment
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Assessment Subject Area shows the types of assessments that apply to the insurance and financial business. These provide for oversight, risk assessment, financial information and valuation of assets. Assessments are related to other major entities such as agreement, insurable object and claim, with party roles for assessment being defined in the common metaphor.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: B1 - Agreement Role
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Agreement Role Subject Area shows examples of the roles that can be involved in agreements. While these roles would become Role Codes in an implementation, it is usable to display them for understanding.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: B2 - Claim Role
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Claim Role Subject Area shows examples of the roles that can be involved in claims. While these roles would become Role Codes in an implementation, it is usable to display them for understanding.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: B3 - Staffing Role
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Staffing Role Subject Area shows examples of the roles that can be involved in staffing. While these roles would become Role Codes in an implementation, it is usable to display them for understanding. This subject area also shows the entities of interest with respect to the classification and assignment of staff, which supports the operational aspects of insurance and financial services.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: C1 - Party Subtype
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Party Subtype Subject Area shows examples of the classifications of organization and group. It also provides examples of the use of organization and the optional ways of defining organization hierarchies. The use of party relationship is demonstrated as a common way of managing party person, organization, and group relationships.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: C2 - Insurable Object Subtype
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Insurable Object Subtype Subject Area shows examples of the varied objects that can be involved in insurance. Some subtypes require further specialized information and may involve implementation of the subtypes, whereas some objects can be commonly described at the object level.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: C3 - Money Subtype
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The "Money" Subtype Subject Area shows the various classifications of policy and claim monies, and is useful for the understanding of what is represented in the Policy Amount and Claim Amount entities.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: C4 - Event Subtype
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Event Subject Area shows the subtypes of events defined to date for policy.

CWMXER:SubjectArea.name: D1 - Product Coverage Reference
CWMXER:SubjectArea.shortDescription: The Product Coverage Reference Subject Area shows the entities involved in defining the company products and coverages. This is the framework for defining master data for the offerings of the company, and assuring integrity of the policy data.

CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Coverage Type defines the categories for different types of coverages, e.g. is the coverage for liability, for physical damage, for no fault.

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Type Identifier is the unique identifier of a Coverage Type.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Type Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Type Description is the textual description of the Coverage Type.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Type Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Type Name is the name given to the Coverage Type, e.g. Liability, Property, No Fault.

CWM:Description.name: Note for COVERAGE TYPE
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: CREDIT RATING
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Credit Rating is a rating typically provided by a financial institution or rating service indicating the likelihood of a Party to meet financial commitments based on past behavior and current financial position.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWM:Description.name: Note for CREDIT RATING
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: IBM's IAA; OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: CUSTOMER SCORE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Customer Score is a kind of Assessment Result that assigns points to each customer based on specific criteria in order to be able to rank order customers against the dependent variable measured by that criteria.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Catastrophe
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Catastrophe is a destructive event of significant importance. Due to both the scope and the scale of losses under the event, it is classified separately from other loss events. These events may also be formally classified by a political entity whose jurisdiction the event took place.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Catastrophe Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Catastrophe Identifier is the unique identifier for a Catastrophe.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Catastrophe Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Catastrophe Type Code represents the type of severe loss characterized by extreme force and/or sizable financial loss.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Catastrophe Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Catastrophe Name is the wording assigned to a catastrophe by regulatory agency or Insurance Company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Industry Catastrophe Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Industry Catastrophe Code is a code assigned by regulatory agency to identify a single major loss occurring on a specified date or to a single loss incurred over a number of days.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Company Catastrophe Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Company Catastrophe Code is the Code assigned to a Catastrophe by the Company.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Ceded Claim Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Ceded Claim Amount identifies claim monies as being owed by a reinsurer.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Ceded Policy Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Ceded Policy Amount identifies policy monies as being owed to a reinsurer.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Claim Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Claim Amount is the money being paid or collected for settling a claim and paying the claimants, reinsurers, other insurers, and other interested parties. Claim amounts are classified by various attributes.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Offer Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Offer Identifier is the unique identifier for a Claim Offer.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Identifier is the unique identifier for a Claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Amount Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Amount Type Code defines the category to which a monetary amount will be applied. Example: premium, commission, taxes, surcharge.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Date is the date on which a transaction or insurance-related happening takes place.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount is the financial amount reserved or paid in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurance Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurance Type Code represents the category under which risk is assumed. Examples: Direct for policies directly issued by a company; Assumed for risks assumed from another company; Ceded for portions of risk ceded to another insurer.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Claim Arbitration
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Claim Arbitration is an associative entity that relates a Claim to an Arbitration.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Identifier is the unique identifier for a Claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Arbitration Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Arbitration Identifier is the unique identifier of a dispute resolution mechanism designed to help aggrieved parties recover damages.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Claim Assessment
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Claim Assessment is an associative entity that relates a Claim to an Assessment.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Identifier is the unique identifier for a Claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Identifier is the unique identifier of a grouping of Assessments such as a Person or Object.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Claim Coverage
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Claim Coverage is an associative entity that relates a Claim to the Policy Coverage under which the claim is paid.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Identifier is the unique identifier for a Claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier is the unique identifier of each of the specific coverages within a Policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Claim Evaluation Result
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Claim Evaluation Result is the outcome of a Claim Assessment.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Claim Event
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Claim Event is a subtype of Event that identifies and describes the accident or occurrence that triggered the claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Claim Folder Document
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Claim Folder Supporting Document is written information such as agreements, financial statements, offers, proposals, etc., to provide backup and depth to agreed-upon or discussed claim matters.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Document Sequence Number
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Document Sequence Number defines the order in which documents are presented.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Identifier is the unique identifier for a Claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Document Link Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Document Link Value is an electronic address that identifies the location of a document.

CWM:Description.name: Note for Claim Folder Document
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: BusinessDictionary.com

CWMXER:Entity.name: Claim Litigation
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Claim Litigation is a legal proceeding that may be a lawsuit about a claim or a settlement out of court.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Identifier is the unique identifier for a Claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Litigation Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Litigation Identifier uniquely identifies a process of filing a lawsuit in the appropriate jurisdiction to settle a legal dispute or controversy through which legal rights are sought to be determined and enforced.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Communication Identity
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Communication Identity provides contact information specifications that can be utilized for communicating with a party. It specifies Communication Type (e.g., physical address, email, phone, Facebook) and Communication Value (e.g., phone number, email address, site address).

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Communication Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Communication Identifier is the unique identifier for a communication specification used to contact a party, such as a telephone number or address.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Communication Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Communication Type Code represents the kind of communication.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Communication Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Communication Value is the value assigned to a communication mechanism. Examples: the characters of the phone number or email address.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Communication Qualifier Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Communication Qualifier Value further describes a communication specification such as a telephone extension, or a floor or room number within a building.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Company Jurisdiction
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Company Jurisdiction is a legal entity or recognized political subdivision that defines where an insurance company can operate and which products can be sold and serviced by the company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Company Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Company Identifier is a unique identifier for a company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Consultant Contract
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Consultant Contract is a subtype of Agreement that outlines the working arrangement for a consultant.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Coverage Group
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Coverage Group is the aggregation of coverage under a broader business classification to group them for reporting purposes, e.g. a group of liability coverage, a group of property coverage.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Group Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Group Identifier is a unique identifier for a Coverage Group.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Group Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Group Description is text that provides more detail about Coverage Group.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Group Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Group Name is the name given to the grouping of coverages.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Coverage Level
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Coverage Level is one of the possible limits of indemnification provided under a coverage.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Level Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Level Identifier is a unique identifier of the Coverage Level definition.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Limit Type Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Limit Type Identifier is a unique identifier of a Coverage Limit Type.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Maximum Per Person Amount
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Maximum Per Person Amount is the Limit that can be paid to any person for the specified coverage per claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Aggregate Limit Amount
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Aggregate Limit Amount is a limit of coverage that specifies the maximum amount (or other limit expression such as number of days) to be paid regardless of any other factor.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Maximum Per Claim Amount
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Maximum Per Claim Amount is the Limit that can be paid for any single event for which a claim is reported. This amount is inclusive of all coverage provided by an insurance policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Deductible Rate
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Deductible Rate is a rating factor used to calculate the premium charge for the deductible based on the Coverage Level and Deductible selected.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Label Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Label Name is a consistent short name used to identify a coverage on documents and reports.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Identifier is the unique identifier of a Coverage.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Coverage Limit Type
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Coverage Limit Type is the category of indemnification limit that is applied under a coverage.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Limit Type Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Limit Type Identifier is a unique identifier of a Coverage Limit Type.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Limit Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Limit Name is the name given to the Coverage Limit Type, e.g. Specified Amount, Insurance to Value.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Limit Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Limit Description is the textual description of the Coverage Limit.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Coverage Part
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Coverage Part is a section of an insurance Policy that organizes coverages at a high level, usually property versus liability.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Part Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Part Code is an abbreviation for the Coverage Part of an insurance policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Part Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Part Name is the wording used to distinguish a Coverage Part of a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Credit Claim Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Credit Claim Amount is any Claim Amount that offsets the amount paid for a claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Credit Policy Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Credit Policy Amount is any Policy Amount that offsets the revenue for a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: DEDUCTIBLE RECOVERY
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Deductible Recovery is a subtype of Claim Amount that represents from the individual responsible for the deductible payment the amount of deductible associated with a loss payment under a claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: DEMOGRAPHIC SCORE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Demographic Score is an Assessment Result that is used to rank orders, risks, or individuals based on a table of points assigned to pre-identified demographic characteristics of the risk or individual.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: DEPARTMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Department is an Organization Unit that groups individuals with common or related jobs to accomplish certain common or related functions. Example: payroll department.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Department Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Department Identifier is a subtype of Party Identifier for an Organization that is a Department.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWM:Description.name: Note for DEPARTMENT
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: Barron's Dictionary of Insurance Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: DERIVATIVE CONTRACT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Derivative Contract is a kind of Agreement where the value of the contract is based on derived variables or characteristics, such as an index of commodity prices.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWMXER:Entity.name: DWELLING
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Dwelling is an Insured Object that is a structure or part of a structure used as a place of residence by human beings.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for DWELLING
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Barron's Dictionary of Business Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: Debit Claim Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Debit Claim Amount is any amount that is paid for a claim, including monies paid to claimants and claim expenses.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Debit Policy Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Debit Policy Amount is any amount that is owed to the company for insurance (called premium), or taxes and surcharges.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Direct Claim Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Direct Claim Amount classifies monies as belonging to a claim that relates to a policy that is directly written by the company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Direct Policy Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Direct Policy Amount classifies monies as belonging to a Policy that is written directly by the company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: ENDORSEMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Endorsement is a supplementary coverage option added to the base policy in order to expand or extend the coverage provided. From a financial perspective, endorsements may have an effect on the total premium paid for a policy, or may not have an impact on the premium paid for the policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Employment Agreement
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Employment Agreement is a written Agreement between employer and employee, stating the terms of employment in an organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Event
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Event is anything that happens, or is contemplated as happening. From an insurance perspective, an event is a situation that may impact the risk or indemnification covered by a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Expense Payment
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Expense Payment is the amount paid for the expenses to settle a claim in whole or in part.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Expense Recovery
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Expense Recovery is the reimbursement of part or all of an Expense Payment.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Expense Reserve
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Expense Reserve is the amount set aside for the expected expenses to settle a Claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: FARM EQUIPMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Farm Equipment is an Insured Object that is Equipment commonly used on a Farm, for example a tractor, cultivator, plow, combine, grain elevator, milking machine, etc.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for FARM EQUIPMENT
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: FINANCIAL SERVICES ASSESSMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Financial Services Assessment is a kind of Assessment Result that focuses on the finances of an individual or organization based on pre-defined characteristics that identify the financial or monetary risks represented by the firm.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: FINANCIAL VALUATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Financial Valuation is an assessment result expressed in financial units.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWM:Description.name: Note for FINANCIAL VALUATION
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: IBM's IAA

CWMXER:Entity.name: FLAT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Flat is a Cancellation Event subtype that represents the full cancellation of a policy where the policy is deemed to have never existed, no risk indemnification has been provided, and a full return of premium is granted.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: For Profit Organization is a subtype of Organization and Party that is a means of classifying an organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWMXER:Entity.name: FREIGHT GROUP
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Freight Group is a kind of Insurable Object Group that addresses responsibility for in transit goods.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Entity.name: FULL TERM
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Full term is a type of endorsement where the changes made are effective on the policy effective date and apply for the full term of the policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Fee
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Fee is a charge imposed on the insurance company on an insurance policy either as a service fee and/or from a government entity as a tax on the premium charged.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Field Organization Unit
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Sales Organization Unit is an example of the use of Party to define a company's internal organization geographic locations, usually to support sales and marketing operations.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWM:Description.name: Note for Field Organization Unit
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: Financial Account Agreement
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Financial Account Agreement is a kind of Agreement that is between a financial services provider and an account holder and is related to the management of a financial account.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWM:Description.name: Note for Financial Account Agreement
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: IBM's IAA

CWMXER:Entity.name: Fraud Assessment
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Fraud Assessment is a subtype of Assessment Result that identifies whether fraud has occured or is occuring, the extent and impact of the fraud, and to determine who is responsible for the fraud.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: GEOGRAPHIC LOCATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Geographic Location is a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that may or may not be a structured address, Examples: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area, postal address, property address.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Parent Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Parent Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a recursive higher level bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Type Code represents the type of Geographic Location, e.g. a State or a county, or a building location.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Location Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Location Code is assigned externally by an insured party to represent one of their locations.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Location Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Location Name is the wording assigned to name a place.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Location Number
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Location Number is a number assigned and used internally by an insured party to identify one of their locations.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: State Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: State Code is a two character representation of a U.S. state or Canadian Province.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Location Address Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Location Address Identifier is assigned by the insurance carrier to uniquely identify a physical site that generally includes street number, street, city, state/province, postal code, and country. This location can be a structure that contains a home, commercial building, vehicle or items to be insured, as well as a site where a party can recieve mail.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Physical Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Physical Location Identifier is the unique identifier for a Physical Location.

CWM:Description.name: Note for GEOGRAPHIC LOCATION
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: GOVERNMENT ORGANIZATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Government Organization is a kind of Organization with control of any asset, industry, or enterprise at any level, national, regional or local (municipal).

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWMXER:Entity.name: GROUP AGREEMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Group Agreement is a kind of contractual insurance Agreement provided to the employer and detailing coverage provided to the group.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Grouping
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Grouping is an informal collection of people banded together through a common situation. Example: Household or Project Team or professional group.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Grouping Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Group Identifier is the unique Party Identifier of a Group, which is a subtype of Party.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Grouping Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Group Name is the name assigned to a Group.

CWMXER:Entity.name: HOUSEHOLD
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Household is a set of individuals, usually resident at the same address, and members of the same nuclear or extended family, who share a common economic interest and who are to be treated for certain purposes (for example, marketing campaigns) as a unit.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Household Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Household Identifier is the unique identifier of a Household, and, as a subtype of Group, is also a Group and Party Identifier.

CWM:Description.name: Note for HOUSEHOLD
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; IBM's IAA

CWMXER:Entity.name: HOUSEHOLD CONTENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Household Content is a categorization and description of all Insurable Objects (personal property) within a residence, which details all items covered and indemnified in the event an insurance claim must be filed.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Household Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Household Identifier is the unique identifier of a Household, and, as a subtype of Group, is also a Group and Party Identifier.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item frelevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for HOUSEHOLD CONTENT
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Barron's Dictionary of Business Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: Household Person
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Household Person is an individual who resides within a household.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Household Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Household Identifier is the unique identifier of a Household, and, as a subtype of Group, is also a Group and Party Identifier.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Person Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Person Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as a person.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Household Person Role
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Household Person Role defines an individual's function within a household, such as head of household.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Household Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Household Identifier is the unique identifier of a Household, and, as a subtype of Group, is also a Group and Party Identifier.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Role Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Role Code is an abbreviation of name of the role that a Party plays with respect to another entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Begin Date is a date used throughout the model to reflect the best known date on which the related data was recorded or changed. It may be the date of change notification, the date of change was entered to a system (preferably the system of record), or the date that the related database was updated. The date that is used should be consistent throughout the implemented solution.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: End Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: End Date is the year, month, and day on which the associated data is no longer relevant or is scheduled to stop.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Person Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Person Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as a person.

CWMXER:Entity.name: INDIVIDUAL AGREEMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Individual Agreement is a kind of legal or contractual Agreement that an Individual voluntarily enters.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWMXER:Entity.name: INSURED ACCOUNT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Insured Account is an account at a brokerage firm, bank, savings and loan association or credit union that is insured either by a federal or private insurance. This could also be an organization that has one or more contractual relationships with a commercial lines insurer.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Account Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Account Identifier is the unique identifier of an Account

CWMXER:Entity.name: INTERMEDIARY AGREEMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: An Intermediary Agreement is a kind of Agreement that defines the ways in which an intermediary can act on behalf of an insurance company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWM:Description.name: Note for INTERMEDIARY AGREEMENT
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: Insurable Object
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: An Insurable Object is an item which may be included or excluded from an insurance coverage or policy, either as the object for which possible damages of the object or loss of the object is insured, or as the object for which damages caused by the object are insured. Examples: residence, vehicle, class of employees.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Type Code represents a category of an item figuring in an insurance coverage or policy, having commercial or exchange value that is owned by a business, institution, or individual or adds to one's wealth or estate. These objects can be real (land and attachments) and personal (movable effects not attached to land).

CWM:Description.name: Note for Insurable Object
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; ACORD

CWMXER:Entity.name: Insurable Object Party Role
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Insurable Object Party Role defines how the Party and the Insurable Object are related. Examples: person is driver of vehicle, organization owns property.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Role Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Role Code is an abbreviation of name of the role that a Party plays with respect to another entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Expiration Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Expiration Date is the year, month, and day when a contractual term or coverage is ended or when a policy expires.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Insurance Class
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Insurance Class is the high level type or line of insurance business in which the organization is engaged, e.g. Property and Casualty or Life Insurance.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurance Class Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurance Class Identifier is the unique identifier for an Insurance Class.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurance Class Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurance Class Name is the name given to the Insurance Class.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurance Class Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurance Class Description is the textual description of the Insurance Class.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Insurance Rating Classification Code
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Insurance Rating Classification Code is a Code that varies by insurance line of business and is used to define the rate for calculating premiums for various coverages, types of insurable objects, and locations.

CWMXER:Entity.name: LITIGATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Litigation is a judicial contest through which legal rights are sought to be determined and enforced.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Litigation Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Litigation Identifier uniquely identifies a process of filing a lawsuit in the appropriate jurisdiction to settle a legal dispute or controversy through which legal rights are sought to be determined and enforced.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Court Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Court Identifier is a unique identifier for each court name and jurisdiction.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Jurisdiction Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Jurisdiction Identifier uniquely identifies a geographic or topical area of authority for a specific government entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Litigation Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Litigation Description is the text verbiage used to define the type or extent of litigation.

CWM:Description.name: Note for LITIGATION
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: Barron's Dictionary of Business Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: Legal Jurisdiction
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Legal Jurisdiction is a geographic or topical area of authority for a specific government entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Legal Jurisdiction Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Legal Jurisdiction Identity uniquely identifies a geographic or topical area of authority for a specific government entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Legal Jurisdiction Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Legal Jurisdiction Name is the wording assigned to a geographic or topical area of authority for a specific government entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Legal Jurisdiction Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Leal Jurisdiction Description defines a geographic or topical area of authority for a specific government entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Rules Reference Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Rules Reference Description is the text used to refer or link to rules related to the entity.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Legal Jurisdiction Party Identity
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Legal Jurisdiction Party Identity provides the identifier by which a party is known to the designated legal jurisdiction, such as a drivers license number for a given state jurisdiction.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Legal Jurisdiction Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Legal Jurisdiction Identity uniquely identifies a geographic or topical area of authority for a specific government entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Legal Entity Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Legal Entity Type Code represents a category of person or organization that has the legal standing to enter into a contract and may be sued for failure to perform as agreed in the contract. It can be a type of partnership, corporation, or other organization having the capacity to negotiate contracts, assume financial obligations, and pay off debts. Examples: Stock, Mutual, Fraternal, Reciprocal Exchange.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Legal Classification Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Legal Classification Code represents a legal category under which the Party can operate.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Legal Jurisdiction Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Legal Jurisdiction Party Identifier is the Legal Jurisdiction's Identifier for a Party. Example: State of PA. Taxpayer ID for a Company.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Life Event
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Life Event is an incident that occurs during the lifetime of a Party and that may have importance in a decision by the party to contemplate the purchase of insurance, e.g. the birth of a child, a birthday, a graduation event.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Line of Business
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Line of Business is the kind of insurance business in which the organization is engaged, e.g. property, liability, life, health.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Identifier uniquely identifies a major kind of insurance product, such as automobile, business owners, etc.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Name is the identifying label given to a line of business by the company, or by insurance organizations and regulators. Examples: P&C, Oil & Natural Gas, Fixed Income Investments.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Description is the textual description of the line of business coverage, e.g. Commercial Property, Commercial Auto.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Code represents the line of business, or how the insured wants to track their products, e.g. CP - Commercial Property, CA - Commercial Auto.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Group Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Group Identifier is a unique identifier for a set of Lines of Business that can be grouped for reporting and analysis.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurance Class Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurance Class Identifier is is the unique identifier for an Insurance Class.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Line of Business Group
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Line of Business Group is the aggregation of insurance coverages or contracts by an insurance carrier, either for internal reporting purposes or external reporting purposes.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Group Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Group Identifier is a unique identifier for a set of Lines of Business that can be grouped for reporting and analysis.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Group Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Group Name is the textual description of Line of Business Group.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Group Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Group Description is the textual description of the Line of business group.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Litigation Party Role
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Litigation Party Role defines how the Party relates to a Litigation case.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Litigation Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Litigation Identifier uniquely identifies a process of filing a lawsuit in the appropriate jurisdiction to settle a legal dispute or controversy through which legal rights are sought to be determined and enforced.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Role Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Role Code is an abbreviation of name of the role that a Party plays with respect to another entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Begin Date is a date used throughout the model to reflect the best known date on which the related data was recorded or changed. It may be the date of change notification, the date of change was entered to a system (preferably the system of record), or the date that the related database was updated. The date that is used should be consistent throughout the implemented solution.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: End Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: End Date is the year, month, and day on which the associated data is no longer relevant or is scheduled to stop.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Identifier is the unique identifier for a Claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Location Address
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Postal Address is a Contact Point that is an address used for the delivery of letters and packages by an external mailing or packaging service, at a place where the recipient usually lives or works. Note that the exact structure of a postal address is likely to change depending on the country of the postal address.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line 1 Address
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line 1 Address is the initial line of an address usually providing a building identifier and a street.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Municipality Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Municipality Name is the wording used to identify limited geographic area responsible for maintenance of throughways as well as a myriad of public services.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line 2 Address
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line 2 Address is the second line of an address that further qualifies an address. Example: XYZ Building Suite 123 or Apt F.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Postal Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Postal Code represents an alphanumeric code assigned to groups of addresses by various national postal systems throughout the world to facilitate mail delivery.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Country Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Country Code is an abbreviation that is unique for each country.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: State Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: State Code is a two character representation of a U.S. state or Canadian Province.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Location Address Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Location Address Identifier is assigned by the insurance carrier to uniquely identify a physical site that generally includes street number, street, city, state/province, postal code, and country. This location can be a structure that contains a home, commercial building, vehicle or items to be insured, as well as a site where a party can recieve mail.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Begin Date is a date used throughout the model to reflect the best known date on which the related data was recorded or changed. It may be the date of change notification, the date of change was entered to a system (preferably the system of record), or the date that the related database was updated. The date that is used should be consistent throughout the implemented solution.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: End Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: End Date is the year, month, and day on which the associated data is no longer relevant or is scheduled to stop.

CWM:Description.name: Note for Location Address
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: IBM's IAA

CWMXER:Entity.name: Loss Payment
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Loss Payment is the amount paid to claimants to settle a claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Loss Recovery
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Loss Recovery is the reimbursement of part or all of a Loss Payment.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Loss Reserve
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Loss Reserve is the amount set aside for expected loss over the life of the Claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: MANUFACTURED OBJECT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Manufactured Object is an Insurable Object that was made by machine or by industrial process.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Entity.name: MEDICAL CONDITION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Medical Condition is an assessment of the health state and physical condition of person, that may be covered or indemnified by an insurance policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWM:Description.name: Note for MEDICAL CONDITION
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: MID TERM
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Mid Term is a type of endorsement that is applied to a policy whereby the changes are made and effective at a point in time after the effective date and before the expiration date of a policy term, and not from the effective date of the policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: MILKING MACHINE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Milking Machine is an Insurable Object that is a kind of Farm Equipment and is an electric machine for milking cows.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Entity.name: MOBILE HOME
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Mobile Home is an Insured Object that is a dwelling unit manufactured in a factory and designed to be transported to a site and semi permanently attached.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for MOBILE HOME
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Barron's Dictionary of Business Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: MOTORCYCLE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Motorcycle is an Insured Object that is a two or three wheeled automotive vehicle for one or two people.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for MOTORCYCLE
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Merriam Webster

CWMXER:Entity.name: NEW BUSINESS
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: New Business is a policy transaction by which an insurance policy is purchased by or sold to an individual or organization where no current relationship exists for that policy type with the insurance company. This operation is recognized when the first premium is collected.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Not For Profit Organization is a kind of Organization that has received a current and appropriate government designation as a Not for Profit entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWMXER:Entity.name: OBJECT ASSESSMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Object Assessment is the review and evaluation of a specific insured item for validation of coverage.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Identifier is the unique identifier of a grouping of Assessments such as a Person or Object.

CWMXER:Entity.name: ORGANIZATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: An Organization is a Party that is a business concern or a group of individuals that are systematically bound by a common purpose. Organizations may be legal entities in their own right. Examples: commercial organizations such as limited companies, publicly quoted multinationals, subsidiaries.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Industry Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Industry Code is an external classification of industries, such as an SIC (Standard Industry Classification Code). Example: 63nnnnnn is the classification series for Insurance Carriers.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Name is the wording used to identify an Organization and should be the legal name for the organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Dun And Bradstreet Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Dun and Bradstreet Identifier is the unique DUNS Number identifier assigned to a legal entity by Dun & Bradstreet.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Type Code is used to distinguish various types of internal and external organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Alternate Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Alternate Name is an alias or additional name used by an Organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Description is text used to describe an Organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Acronym Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Acronym Name is an abbreviated version of an Organization's name. Example: IBM, SMS, NBC.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Industry Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Industry Type Code represents an Industry category that is important to the company. Example: Financial Institution, Healthcare.

CWM:Description.name: Note for ORGANIZATION
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; ACORD

CWMXER:Entity.name: ORGANIZATION UNIT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: An Organization Unit is a Division, Department, Territory or any other entity that is used to manage company operations. Some but not all Organization Units are legal entities.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Unit Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Unit Name is the formal and distinct name for an organization unit within an overall Organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Unit Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Unit Description provides distinguishing characteristics for the specific unit.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Industry Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Industry Code is an external classification of industries, such as an SIC (Standard Industry Classification Code). Example:Example: 63nnnnnn is the classification series for Insurance Carriers.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Accounting Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Accounting Code is the budget or general ledger code that can apply to any monies of a business.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Work Site Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Work Site Type Code defines the kind of workplace. Example: Office Building, Plant, Farm.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWM:Description.name: Note for ORGANIZATION UNIT
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: IBM's IAA

CWMXER:Entity.name: OTHER ASSESSMENT RESULT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Other Assessment Result is a kind of Assessment Result that is not covered by other commonly listed options available.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Occurrence
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Occurrence is an event that results in bodily injury and/or property damage to a third party. A clause that is common to most liability insurance policies stipulates that all bodily injuries and/or property damages resulting from the same general conditions are interpreted as resulting from one occurrence and thus subject to the policy limits per occurrence.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Catastrophic Event Indicator
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Catastrophic Event Indicator indicates that an occurrence is the result of a severe loss characterized by extreme force and/or sizable financial loss.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Occurrence Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Occurrence Begin Date is the date that a potential loss event commenced.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Occurrence End Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Occurrence End Date is the date that marks the ending of an event occurrence.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Occurrence Begin Time
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Occurrence Begin Time is the time of day at which a potential loss event commenced.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Occurrence End Time
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Occurrence End Time is the time of day at which an event occurrence ceased.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Occurrence Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Occurrence Name is the wording used to provide a familiar label for an event occurrence.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Occurrence Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Occurrence Identifier uniquely identifies an event occurrence.

CWMXER:Entity.name: PARTY
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Party is a Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, or which plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Name is the wording used to name and (at least partially) identify a Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, or play a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Begin Date is a date used throughout the model to reflect the best known date on which the related data was recorded or changed. It may be the date of change notification, the date of change was entered to a system (preferably the system of record), or the date that the related database was updated. The date that is used should be consistent throughout the implemented solution.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: End Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: End Date is the year, month, and day on which the associated data is no longer relevant or is scheduled to stop.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Type Code is an abbreviation that defines the kind of Party. Example: Person, Organization, Grouping.

CWM:Description.name: Note for PARTY
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; ACORD

CWMXER:Entity.name: PERSON
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Person is a Party who is a human being, either alive or dead.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Person Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Person Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as a person.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: First Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: First Name is the given name of a Person Party.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Middle Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Middle name is a second name used by an individual to further differentiate their name, and is often represented with an initial.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Last Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Last Name is the family name of an Individual Party.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Full Legal Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Full Legal Name is the name of a Person or Organization party, spelled out in full. Example: John D. Smith, Ph.D.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Nickname
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Nickname is a shorter version of a person's name or an alternate name by which the person prefers to be addressed. Example: Bill for William.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Suffix Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Suffix Name is an extension added to the end of a name to further qualify it. Examples: M.D, PhD, Jr, Sr, III.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Birth Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Birth Date is the year, month, and day that a person was born.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Birth Place Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Birth Place Name is the city and state, province, prefecture, land, county (or other general areas) or country in which a person was born.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Gender Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Gender Code represents the sex of an Individual. Values are F= Female, M = Male and U = Unknown or Not Applicable.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Prefix Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Prefix Name is the title added to the beginning of a name to further qualify. Examples: Mr., Mrs., Ms, Dr.

CWM:Description.name: Note for PERSON
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: IBM's IAA

CWMXER:Entity.name: PHYSICAL LOCATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Physical Location is an area bounded by parameters such as Latitude and Longitude, Altitude, Depth, etc.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Physical Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Physical Location Identifier is the unique identifier for a Physical Location.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Physical Location Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Physical Location Name is name given to the physical location of the property, e.g. Rockefeller Center.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Latitude Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Latitude Value is the value on a grid of the globe that locates the point horizontally East to West.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Longitude Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Longitude Value is the value on a grid of the globe that locates the point Vertically north to south.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Altitude Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Altitude Value is the vertical distance or height measured upward from sea level to a point in the atmosphere.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Altitude Mean Sea Level Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Altitude Mean Sea Level Value is the average sea level height.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Horizontal Accuracy Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Horizontal Accuracy Value defines the horizontal location for a property, e.g. 1.000 feet from the hydrant.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Vertical Accuracy Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Vertical Accuracy Value is the height of a location, for example 4,000 foot height up the mountain.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Travel Direction Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Travel Direction Description provides the instructions for driving to a particular location.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Location Address Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Location Address Identifier is assigned by the insurance carrier to uniquely identify a physical site that generally includes street number, street, city, state/province, postal code, and country. This location can be a structure that contains a home, commercial building, vehicle or items to be insured, as well as a site where a party can recieve mail.

CWM:Description.name: Note for PHYSICAL LOCATION
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: PHYSICAL OBJECT ASSESSMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Physical Object Assessment is an assessment type that measures the risks represented by ownership, utilization or proximity of the physical object. It collects information regarding the likelihood of the object to contribute to the probability of future loss under an insurance policy or contract issued.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: PLACE ASSESSMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Place Assessment is information regarding a location and/or physical structure that may impact its likelihood to contribute to the probability of future events that may increase the risk under an insurance policy or contract issued.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: POLICY
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Policy is a kind of written Agreement that puts insurance coverage into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Expiration Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Expiration Date is the year, month, and day when a contractual term or coverage is ended or when a policy expires.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Number
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Number is the external identification for a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Status Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Status Code represents the state of the related entity at a point in time. Examples: A = Active, P = Pending, C = Cancelled, T = Terminated.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Identifier is the unique identifier of a policy.

CWM:Description.name: Note for POLICY
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: Barron's Dictionary of Insurance Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: POLICY RELATIONSHIP
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Policy Relationship defines the relationship between two policies.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Identifier is the unique identifier of a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Relationship Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Relationship Code represents a relationship that ties entities together.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Expiration Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Expiration Date is the year, month, and day when a contractual term or coverage is ended or when a policy expires.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Related Policy identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Related Policy Identifier is the unique identifier of a policy that is related to another policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: PRE QUALIFICATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Pre Qualification is an Event resulting from the process of assuring that a risk will be acceptable and a policy will be issued before either the application is recieved or the policy is fully underwritten.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: PREMIUM
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Premium is money amount that is charged for the amount of insurance and the coverage terms provided under the policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: PRO RATA
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Pro Rata is a type of cancellation Event where the policy is deemed to have been effective for a period of time and only a pro rata amount of premium is returned based on the time the policy was effective. The calculation methodology for the pro rata amount can change from insurance company to insurance company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: PROPERTY IN TRANSIT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Property in Transit is a kind of Insured Object Group that is property being transported in any vehicle.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for PROPERTY IN TRANSIT
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: PROVIDER AGREEMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Provider Agreement is a kind of Agreement between an individual or organization which provides products and/or services, and the individual or organization contracting for the products and/or services.
