CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Party Assessment
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Party Assessment is an associative entity that relates a Party to an Assessment.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Person Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Person Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as a person.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Identifier is the unique identifier of a grouping of Assessments such as a Person or Object.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Party Communication
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Party Communication links a party to a Communication Identity. Examples; a person has a phone number; an organization has a website: both have an address.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Begin Date is a date used throughout the model to reflect the best known date on which the related data was recorded or changed. It may be the date of change notification, the date of change was entered to a system (preferably the system of record), or the date that the related database was updated. The date that is used should be consistent throughout the implemented solution.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: End Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: End Date is the year, month, and day on which the associated data is no longer relevant or is scheduled to stop.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Communication Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Communication Identifier is the unique identifier for a communication specification used to contact a party, such as a telephone number or address.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Locality Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Locality Code represents the physical location of the party.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Preference Sequence Number
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Preferred Sequence Number is a relatively assigned order of an entry listed within another qualifying attribute for a Party's preference.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Preference Day and Time Group Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Preference Day and Time Group Code represents the day and/or time that a party prefers to be contacted.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Routing Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Routing Description is the text definition of how information is to be sent to a party.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Party Preference
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Party Preference records preferences (in addition to communication ones) such as language for persons or groups.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Preferred Language Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Preferred Language Code is the designation for the language of choice for an Organization, Person, or Grouping.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWM:Description.name: Note for Party Preference
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: Party Relationship
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Party Relationship defines how two parties are linked to each other, such as person works for an organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Related Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Related Party Identifier is the unique identifier of a relationship between one party and another party.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Begin Date is a date used throughout the model to reflect the best known date on which the related data was recorded or changed. It may be the date of change notification, the date of change was entered to a system (preferably the system of record), or the date that the related database was updated. The date that is used should be consistent throughout the implemented solution.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: End Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: End Date is the year, month, and day on which the associated data is no longer relevant or is scheduled to stop.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Relationship Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Relationship Type Code represents the kind of relationship that links one entity to another. Example: Business, Family, Reporting.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Party Relationship Role
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Party Relationship Role defines the role that one party plays with respect to another party, such as a person working for an organization plays the role of team leader. Party Relationship defines what a party is; Role defines what a party does.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Identifier is a unique identifier of Person, Organization or Grouping that can enter into a contract or other legal proceeding, and plays a role in the insurance industry.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Related Party Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Related Party Identifier is the unique identifier of a relationship between one party and another party.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Relationship Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Relationship Begin Date is the best known date on which a relationship began.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Relationship Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Relationship Type Code represents the kind of relationship that links one entity to another. Example: Business, Family, Reporting.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Role Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Role Code is an abbreviation of name of the role that a Party plays with respect to another entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Role Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Role Begin Date is the best known date on which a role of a person or organization or grouping begins.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Party Role
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Party Role defines how a Party relates to another entity. Role is the definition of what a Person, Organization, or Grouping DOES whereas Relationship is about what a party IS.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Role Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Role Code is an abbreviation of name of the role that a Party plays with respect to another entity.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Role Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Role Name is the wording used to label a Party Role.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Party Role Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Party Role Description is text that defines how a Party relates to another entity.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Person Profession
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Person Profession is a title or career category that describes how an individual earns a living. Examples: Doctor, Lawyer, Teacher, Carpenter, Entertainer.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Person Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Person Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as a person.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Profession Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Profession Name is the wording used to describe how an individual earns a living. Examples: Doctor, Lawyer, Teacher, Carpenter, Entertainer.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Policy Amount
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Policy Amount is a central entity for defining all the monies associated with a Policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Identifier is the unique identifier of a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Amount Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Amount Type Code defines the category to which a monetary amount will be applied. Example: premium, commission, taxes, surcharge.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Earning Begin Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Earning Begin Date is the date on which earnings will start to be recorded and accumulated for the associated Policy Amount.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Earning End Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Earning End Date is the date on which earnings will stop being recorded and accumulated for the associated Policy Amount.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier is the unique identifier of each of the specific coverages within a Policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount is the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurance Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurance Type Code represents the category under which risk is assumed. Examples: Direct for policies directly issued by a company; Assumed for risks assumed from another company; Ceded for portions of risk ceded to another insurer.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Policy Coverage Detail
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Policy Coverage Detail defines the specifiec coverages within the terms of a Policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Expiration Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Expiration Date is the year, month, and day when a contractual term or coverage is ended or when a policy expires.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Description is a free form text definition of a coverage.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Identifier is the unique identifier of a Coverage.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Part Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Part Code is an abbreviation for the Coverage Part of an insurance policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Identifier is the unique identifier of a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier is the unique identifier of each of the specific coverages within a Policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Inclusion Exclusion Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Inclusion Exclusion Code designates whether a coverage is included or specifically excluded from the related insurance policy.

CWM:Description.name: Note for Policy Coverage Detail
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: Policy Coverage Part
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Policy Coverage Part is a major section of a Policy that organizes the coverages. Typically, there are Coverage Parts for property and liability.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Part Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Part Code is an abbreviation for the Coverage Part of an insurance policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Identifier is the unique identifier of a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Policy Deductible
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Policy Deductible defines the Deductibles (attachment point for coverage) associated with the policy coverages. Deductibles are the loss amounts paid by the insured before insurance payments apply.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Deductible Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Deductible Identifier is the unique identifier of the amount of money that the policyholders must pay out of their pockets before reimbursements from the insurance company begin.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier is the unique identifier of each of the specific coverages within a Policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Deductible Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Deductible Type Code represents the kind of deductible, such as per occurence, per person, etc.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Deductible Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Deductible Value is the actual monetary amount, percentage or time period. Examples: $500, 10%, 90 days.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Deductible Basis Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Deductible Basis Code identifies whether the related Deductible Value is an amount or a percentage or number of days, etc. that will be used to determine what an insured person is expected to pay before reimbursement from the insurance company begins.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Policy Event
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Policy Event is an event that deals with servicing an insurance policy. Examples would include Policy Renewal, Reinstatement, Cancellation, etc.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Date is the date on which a transaction or insurance-related happening takes place.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Type Code represents the kind of an event. Examples: life event, business event, policy event or loss event.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Sub Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Sub Type Code represents a lower categorization of an event. Examples: within a policy event are renewal and cancellation.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Identifier is the unique identifier of a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Policy Form
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Policy Form is a typical document that explains the insurance coverages for a policy. These are usually standard industry forms augmented by insurer-specific cover pages and specialized addendums.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Form Number
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Form Number is the number assigned to the policy form that identifies the form.. This is usually established by the state or by ISO (Insurance Services Office)

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Identifier is the unique identifier of a policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Form Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Form Value is the set of characters used to identify an attachment to a property and casualty policy that makes it operative.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Policy Limit
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Policy Limit defines the Limits (highest amount of coverage or other limit expression such as number of days compensation) associated with the policy coverages.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Effective Date
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Effective Date is a point in time for when a contractual provision commences or goes into effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Limit Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Limit Identifier is the unique identifier for each limit for each coverage, or for the entire policy, that is provided by an insurance policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier is the unique identifier of each of the specific coverages within a Policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Limit Type Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Limit Type Code represents a category of limit coverage that will be provided by an insurance policy. Examples: Per Occurance, Per Person.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Limit Value
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Limit Value is the actual limit amount or percentage that will be provided by an insurance policy.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Limit Basis Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Limit Basis Code represents the basis on which to specify the maximum extent of coverage that will be provided by an insurance policy. Examples: Amount, Percentage, Days.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Product
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Product is the definition of what is agreed between the insurance company and its customers as an item to be purchased as part of an insurance agreement.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Product Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Product Identifier is the unique identifier for a product.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Line of Business Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Line Of Business Identifier uniquely identifies a major kind of insurance product, such as automobile, business owners, etc.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Licensed Product Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Licensed Product Name is the name given to an offering of protection against a risk or a service related to protection that has been authorized by a regulatory agency to be marketed to the public.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Product Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Product Description is the free form text definition that describes a product.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Product Coverage
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Product Coverage is an associative entity that relates a Product to a Coverage. It is a master reference data entity whose data specifies which Coverages apply to which Products.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Coverage Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Coverage Identifier is the unique identifier of a Coverage.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Product Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Product Identifier is the unique identifier for a product.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Product License
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Product License is an associative entity that relates a Product to a Jurisdiction in which the Product is licensed. It is a master reference data entity whose data specifies which Products are licensed in which Jurisdicitions (usually States).

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Company Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Company Identifier is a unique identifier for a company.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Professional Group
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Professional Grouping is a subtype example of a Grouping that is a subtype of Party.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Grouping Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Group Identifier is the unique Party Identifier of a Group, which is a subtype of Party.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Project
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Project is a subtype example of a Grouping that is a subtype of Party.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Grouping Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Group Identifier is the unique Party Identifier of a Group, which is a subtype of Party.

CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Quote is a type of Event that is a price estimate for an insurance policy. The estimate is considered not to be binding.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: RATING TERRITORY
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Rating Territory is a code developed to charge a adequate premium for the risk within that geographic area.

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Rating Territory Identifier is the unique identifier for a Rating Territory.

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Rating Territory Assigning Organization Identifier is the Party Identifier of the Organization that manages the Rating Territory being defined.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Rating Territory Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Rating Territory Code represents a geographic area that is used to determine insurance rates.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Rating Territory Code Set Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Rating Territory Code Set Identifier is the unique identifier for a set of Rating Territory Codes.

CWMXER:Entity.name: RECOVERY
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Recovery is a kind of Claim Financial in which the insurance company attempts to recoup monies distributed in error or monies due it through the actions or inactions of others.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: RECREATIONAL VEHICLE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Recreational Vehicle is an Insured Object that is a vehicle designed for recreation, as in camping.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for RECREATIONAL VEHICLE
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Merriam Webster

CWMXER:Entity.name: REGIONAL OFFICE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Regional Office is an Organization Unit of an insurance company's operations that may market, underwrite, and service the company's lines of business within a specified geographical area.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Territory Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Territory Identifier is a subtype of Organization which is subtype of Party and is an example of the use of Party to describe a company's organization structure. The Territory definition is often used for marketing or sales territories.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Regional Office Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Regional Officer Identifier is a Party Identifier for a Regional Office that can be a subtype of Organization which is subtype of Party and is an example of the use of Party to describe a company's organization structure.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWM:Description.name: Note for REGIONAL OFFICE
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Barron's Dictionary of Insurance Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: REINSTATEMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Reinstatement is a transaction that is applied to a policy to bring it back to actively insured status from a state where the policy was cancelled.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: REINSURANCE AGREEMENT
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Reinsurance Agreement is a kind of Agreement between the Reinsurer and the Ceding Company that stipulates the manner in which the insurance liability written on various Risks insured by the Ceding Company is to be shared, and the cost of the risk sharing to the Ceding Company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Agreement identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Agreement Identifier is the unique identifier of an Agreement.

CWMXER:Entity.name: REINSURANCE RECOVERY
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Reinsurance Recovery is the act of providing the appropriate information and validation of a loss in order to receive payment from a reinsurance organization providing either facultative or treaty reinsurance.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWMXER:Entity.name: RENEWAL
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Renewal is the action of continuing the coverage provided by a policy from one term to the next when the original term expires.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: RESIDENTIAL STRUCTURE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Residential Structure is an Insured Object that is used for human habitation.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for RESIDENTIAL STRUCTURE
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: RISK FACTOR SCORE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Risk Factor Score is a kind of Assessment Result that evaluates and ranks orders the contribution a common factor has on the underlying Insurable Object.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Rating Territory Geographic Location
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Rating Territory Geographic Location is an associative entity that relates a Rating Territory to a Geographic Location. It is a master reference entity whose data specifies the Geographic Locations within the various Rating Territories.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Geographic Location Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address, for example: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Rating Territory Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Rating Territory Identifier is the unique identifier for a Rating Territory.

CWMXER:Entity.name: SALVAGE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Salvage is the attempt by an Insurance Company to recover value from an object during the handling of a claim.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWM:Description.name: Note for SALVAGE
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts

CWMXER:Entity.name: SCHEDULED ITEM
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Scheduled Item is a kind of Insured Object that is specifically listed in a property insurance contract, and insured seprarately from the standard property insurance in order to receive the full value for a loss. Examples are: Expensive jewelry, furs, paintings, electronics, etc.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for SCHEDULED ITEM
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Barron's Dictionary of Insurance Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: SHORT RATE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Short Rate is a subtype of Cancellation which is a subtype of Policy Event. Short Rate means that when a policy is cancelled, the returned amount of premium is less than the "pro rata" proportion of the time the policy was in effect.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Event Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Event Identifier is a unique identifier of an Event.

CWMXER:Entity.name: STRUCTURE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Structure is an Insured Object that is a man-made building or construction.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.name: Note for STRUCTURE
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: IBM's IAA

CWMXER:Entity.name: SUBROGATION
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Subrogation is the legal process by which an insurance company, after paying a loss, seeks to recover the amount of the loss from another party who is legally liable for it.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Claim Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Claim Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the financial amount reserved, paid, or collected in connection with a claim.

CWM:Description.name: Note for SUBROGATION
CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Barron's Dictionary of Insurance Terms

CWMXER:Entity.name: SURCHARGE
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Surcharge is a charge imposed in excess of standard or normal charges for products and services provided during an insurance activity. The surcharge may be imposed by a governmental organization, an insurance company, or a third party providing goods and services during an insurance event.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Policy Amount Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Staff Classification
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Staff Classification is a designation of staff persons as to benefit eligibility and level within an organization.

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Staff Classification Description is the full position description.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Staff Position
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Staff Position defines the specific job functions in the company.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Staff Position Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Staff Position Identifier is the unique identifier for a Staff Position that is a specific job function.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Staff Position Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Staff Position Name is the job or role title.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Staff Position Description
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Staff Position Description is the full position description

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Staff Classification Code
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Staff Classification Code represents classes of employees versus consultants, based on part and full time, benefit eligibility, etc. for a staff person.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Staff Position Assignment
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Staff Position Assignment is an Organization Unit that is a particular position in an organization which has a job title, responsibilities, and salary range and may have other attributes such as office location, place in the reporting hierarchy, etc.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Staffing Agreement
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Staffing Agreement is a written Agreement between employer and employee, stating the terms of employment in an organization.

CWMXER:Entity.name: State
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: State provides a reference list of U.S. States and Canadian Provinces.

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: State Code is a two character representation of a U.S. state or Canadian Province.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: State Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: State Name is the given name of the State, e.g. Pennsylvania, New York.

CWMXER:Entity.name: TERRITORY
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Territory is a subtype of Organization and is an example of how a company's organization structure can be represented as Party and Party Relationship.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Territory Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Territory Identifier is a subtype of Organization which is subtype of Party and is an example of the use of Party to describe a company's organization structure. The Territory definition is often used for marketing or sales territories.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Organization Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique Party Identifier that is role-named to clarify the party as an organization.

CWMXER:Entity.name: TRACTOR
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Tractor is an Insurable Object that is a kind of Farm Equipment and is a powerful motor-driven vehicle with large, heavy treads used for pulling farm equipment.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Entity.name: TRAILER
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Trailer is an Insured Object that is pulled by another Vehicle and is used for transporting something.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWM:Description.body: Status: Approved Source: OMG Subject Matter Experts; Merriam Webster

CWMXER:Entity.name: TRUCK
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: A Truck is an Insured Object that is any of various motor vehicles designed for carrying or pulling loads.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Insurable Object Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Tax

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier of the monetary value of the insurance coverage premium, fees, commissions and related expenses (such as taxes and surcharges) for a policy.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Team

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Group Identifier is the unique Party Identifier of a Group, which is a subtype of Party.

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Entity.name: Underwriting Assessment
CWMXER:Entity.shortDescription: Underwriting Assessment is an evaluation provided by an Underwriter who is reviewing the proposed new or renewal policy to determine willingness to accept the risk. Items that might be evaluated are the limits of insurance being requested, the demographics of the location, the demographics of the requestor, the condition of the Insurable Object, etc.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Assessment Result Identifier
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Assessment Result Identifier is a unique identifier for the result of an assessment.

CWMXER:Entity.name: VAN

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier of an item relevant to an Insurance coverage or policy as an inclusion or an exclusion.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Vehicle Model Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Vehicle Model Name is the market name for type of vehicle. Example: Accord EX, Blazer.

CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Vehicle Driving Wheel Quantity if the number of wheels that control the vehicle, (2 or 4).

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Vehicle Make Name
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Vehicle Make Name is the market brand name for the maker of the vehicle. Example: Ford, Toyota.

CWMXER:Attribute.name: Vehicle Identification Number
CWMXER:Attribute.shortDescription: Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) in an alphanumeric series that includes make, model, and serial number for each vehicle.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Day
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Day is the numbered date within a Month. Examples: 01-31

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Day_Name
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Day Name is the name of a day in a week.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Day_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Day Type Code is a code that can be used to differentiate between work days, weekend days, and holidays.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Day_And_Time_Group_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Day and Time Group Code represents a general and relative set of time frames. Examples: Week Days during Work Hours, Weekends.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Deductible_Basis_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Deductible Basis Code represents the amount or percentage that will be used to determine the deductible amount an insured is expected to pay out before the insurance company begins reimbursement payments.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Deductible_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Deductible Type Code represents the category of a deductible. Examples: monetary amount, percentage, time period

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Deductible_Value
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Deductible Value is the actual value of a monetary amount, percentage or time period. Examples: $500, 10%, 90 days

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Description
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Description is text that further defines the meaning and use of a code.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Dun_And_Bradstreet_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Dun And Bradstreet Identifier is the unique DUNS Number identifier assigned to a legal entity by Dun & Bradstreet.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Effective_Date
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Effective Date is the date on which something was activated and went into effect.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: End_Date
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: End Date is the month, day and year on which something is scheduled to stop.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Event_Date
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Event Date is the date that an event took place.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Event_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Event Identifier is the unique identifier for an Event.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Event_Sub_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Event Sub Type Code represents a lower level event category.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Event_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Event Type Code represents a category of an event.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Expiration_Date
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Expiration Date is the date on which something is no longer active or valid.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Gender_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Gender Code represents the sex of the individual. Examples: F for female, M for Male, U for Unknown.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Geographic_Location_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Geographic Location Identifier is the unique identifier for a Geographic Location.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Geographic_Location_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Geographic Location Type Code represents a category of a bounded area defined by nature, by an external authority (such as a government) or for an internal business purpose. Used to identify a location in space that is not a structured address. Examples: country, city, continent, postal area, risk area.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Grouping_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Grouping Identifier of the unique Party Identifier for a Grouping.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Identifier is a whole number assigned to uniquely identify an instance within a designated entity.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Inception_Date
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Inception Date is the original effective date of a contract that can be renewed and continue from one time period to another

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Indicator
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Indicator is a one character code that notes if a condition is met or if a situation exists with values of Y = yes, N = no, blank = unknown or not applicable

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Industry_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Industry Code represents an Industry.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Industry_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Industry Type Code represents an Industry category. Examples: Insurance, Banking, Pharmaceutical, Utility

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Insurable_Object_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Insurable Object Identifier is the unique identifier for an Insurable Object.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Insurable_Object_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Insurable Object Type Code represents a category of an item figuring in an insurance coverage or policy, having commercial or exchange value that is owned by a business, institution, or individual or adds to one's wealth or estate. These objects can be real (land and attachments) and personal (movable effects not attached to land).

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Insurance_Class_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Insurance Class Identifier is the unique identifier for an Insurance Class.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Insurance_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Insurance Type Code represents the Insurance Type. Examples: Direct, Assumed, Ceded

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Jurisdiction_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Jurisdiction Identifier is the unique identifier for a Jurisdiction.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Language_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Language Code represents a specific language.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Latitude_Or_Longitude
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Latitude or Longitude is a metric expressed in a common method (expression and precision) to identify a location. The values can be expressed as Degree, Minute, Second, Decimal.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Legal_Classification_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Legal Classification Code represents a legal category under which the Party can operate.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Legal_Entity_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Legal Entity Type Code represents a category of person or organization that has the legal standing to enter into a contract and may be sued for failure to perform as agreed in the contract.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Legal_Jurisdiction_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Legal Jurisdiction Identifier is the unique identifier for a Legal Jurisdiction.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Legal_Jurisdiction_Party_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Legal Jurisdiction Party Identifier is the unique identifier assigned by a Legal Jurisdiction to identify a Party.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Limit_Basis_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Limit Basis Code represents the basis on which to specify the maximum extent of coverage that will be provided by an insurance policy.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Limit_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Limit Type Code represents a category of limit coverage that will be provided by an insurance policy.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Limit_Value
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Limit Value is the actual limit coverage amount that will be provided by an insurance policy.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Line_Of_Business_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Line Of Business Code represents a type of major Product Line. Examples: automobile and home owners insurance.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Line_Of_Business_Group_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Line Of Business Group Identifier is the unique identifier for a Line Of Business Group.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Line_Of_Business_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Line Of Business Identifier is the unique identifier for a Line of Business.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Litigation_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Litigation Identifier is the unique identifier for a Litigation proceeding.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Locality_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Locality Code represents a location category used by a party. Examples: home, work, second residencex

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Location_Address_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Location Address Identifier is the unique identifier for a Location Address.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Location_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Location Code represents an externally assigned identification for a location.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Long_Address
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Long Address is an extra long amount of text that defines a link to a specific webpage or a long electronic address or a long unformatted physical address.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Long_Description
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Long Description is expanded text used to define an object.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Long_Name
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Long Name is the entire legal name of an Organization, Group or full name of an Individual.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Long_Variable_Value
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Long Variable Value is text that can contain syntax or delimiters as needed for interpretation and display, such as a web link. Example: http://www.naic.org/store_jir.htm

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Medium_Address
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Medium Address is averaged sized text that defines a physical or mailing location or an electronic link or address.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Medium_Description
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Medium Description is a generic medium-length text to describe an object.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Medium_Name
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Medium Name is an average length name for codes or non-legal objects.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Month
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Month is the numbered month within a year. Examples: 1-12.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Month_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: A standard 3 position abbreviation for each month of a year.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Month_Name
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Month Name is full English name of a Month.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Name
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Name is the wording used to identify an Organization, Group or full name of an Individual.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Number
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Number is a numeric value that can be expressed as a decimal, exponent, positive or negative value, and against which one can perform arithmetic functions.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Occurrence_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Occurrence Identifier is the unique identifier for an Occurrence.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Organization_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Organization Identifier is the unique identifer for a Party that is an Organization or Organization Unit.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Organization_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Organization Type Code represents an organization category. Values: I = Internal or E = External.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Party_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Party Identifier is the unique identifier for a Party.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Party_Role_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Party Role Code represents the definition of how a Party relates to another entity.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Party_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Party Type Code represents a category of Party. Examples: Person, Organization, Grouping.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Percent
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Percent is a number expressed in relation to a total of 100 percent, in decimal form.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Person_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Person Identifier is the unique identifier for a Party that is a Person.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Physical_Location_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Physical Location Identifier is the unique identifier for a Physical Location.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Policy_Amount_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Policy Amount Identifier is the unique identifier for a Policy Amount.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Policy_Coverage_Detail_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Policy Coverage Detail Identifier is the unique identifier for a Policy Coverage Detail entry.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Policy_Deductible_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Policy Deductible Identifier is the unique identifier for a Policy Deductible entry.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Policy_Form_Value
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Party Form Value is the set of characters used to identify an attachment to a property and casualty policy owned by a party that makes it operative.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Policy_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Policy Identifier is the unique identifier for a Policy.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Policy_Limit_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Policy Limit Identifier is the unique identifier for a Policy Limit entry.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Policy_Number_Value
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Policy Number Value is a value assigned to uniquely identify an insurance policy that can be expressed in letters, numbers or characters

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Postal_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Postal Code represents an alphanumeric code assigned to groups of addresses by various national postal systems throughout the world to facilitate mail delivery

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Prefix_Suffix_Name
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Prefix-Suffix Name is a title or name extension. Examples: Mr., Mrs., Ms., Dr., Jr., Sr., III, M.D., PhD.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Product_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Product Identifier is the unique identifier for a Product.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Quantity
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Quantity is the number of items against which arithmetic functions can be applied.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Quarter
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Quarter is the designated period of time that would represent 1/4th of a year which in sum would add to 4 quarters of a full gregorian year.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Rate
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Rate is a multiplier used to calculate an amount or quantity and is usually expressed as a rate per unit.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Rating_Territory_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Rating Territory Code represents a geographic area that is used to determine insurance rates.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Rating_Territory_Code_Set_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Rating Territory Code Set Identifier is the unique identifier for a set of Rating Territory Codes.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Rating_Territory_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Rating Territory Identifier is the unique identifier for a Rating Territory.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Relationship_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Relationship Code represents a relationship that ties entities together.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Relationship_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Relationship Type Code represents the category of relationship that links one entity to another.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Sequence_Number
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Sequence Number is a relative order of an entry listed within another qualifying attribute.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Short_Address
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Short Address is one line of text or a single address for a physical location or e-mail address.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Short_Description
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Short Description is a generic short text definition for an object

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Short_Name
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Short Name is a brief name used for an object or a partial name of an individual, such as first, last or middle name.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Staff_Classification_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Staff Classification Code represents classes of employees versus consultants, based on part and full time, benefit eligibility, etc. for a staff person.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Staff_Position_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Staff Position Identifier is the unique identifier for Staff Position.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: State_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: State Code is a value used to represent a standard state abbreviation.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Status_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Status Code represents a status. Examples: A = Active, P = Pending, C = Cancelled, T = Terminated.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: String
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: String is free form text with a combination of letters, numbers and characters.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Time
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Time specifies the Hour, Minute, and Second of a 24-hour day.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Variable_Identifier_Value
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Variable Identifier Value is an externally assigned value or identifier. Example: phone number, company site number

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Variable_Value
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Variable Value is an amount, code or any other type of data that can contain syntax (such as hyphen separators) and delimiters as needed for interpretation and display.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Week_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: The code which represents the day of a week.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Work_Site_Type_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Work Site Type Code represents a category of work site. Example: Office, Factory, Plant.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Year
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Year is the number of the year. Example: 1999, 2000, 2020

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Branch_Office_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Branch Office is an Organization Unit that is a local business location of an insurance company that markets and/or services its products and lines of insurance within and to a specified geographic location.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Department_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Department is an Organization Unit that groups individuals with common or related jobs to accomplish certain common or related functions. An example is the Payroll Department.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Industry_Catastrophe_Code
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Industry Catastrophe Code represents a type of catastrophe that is specific to an Industry.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Medium_Variable_Value
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Medium Variable Value is a number, date, or text that may contain syntax or delimiters as needed for interpretation and display. Example: (212) 645-2387, extension 437

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Regional_Office_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: A Regional Office is an Organization Unit of an insurance company's operations that may market, underwrite, and service the company's lines of business within a specified geographical area.

CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.name: Territory_Identifier
CWMRDB:SQLDistinctType.shortDescription: Territory is a subtype of Organization and is an example of how a company's organization structure can be represented as Party and Party Relationship.
